    {
      "type": "note",
      "id": "p4kf8",
      "x": 360,
      "y": 280,
      "name": "note1",
      "width": 300,
      "height": 80,
      "content": "Active/focus state: use $border-focus variable for stroke. Never hardcode #056CFF or #5098FF."
    },
    {
      "type": "note",
      "id": "tPjpb",
      "x": 51472,
      "y": 4307,
      "name": "Save Flow Note",
      "width": 300,
      "height": 220,
      "content": "Save Flow:\n\nWhen the user taps the save icon on the AI response action bar, a popover appears with save options:\n\n1. Save to My Prompts — saves the response directly\n2. Add to Collection — opens a sub-menu to pick a collection\n3. Create New Collection — creates a new collection\n\nAfter saving, a success toast confirms the action."
    },
    {
      "type": "note",
      "id": "HF6lV",
      "x": 50948,
      "y": 4383,
      "width": 300,
      "height": 420,
      "content": "Save Prompt Flow\n\n1. User taps the save icon on a message (user prompt or AI response).\n\n2. A modal appears with:\n   • The prompt/response text in an editable textarea so the user can refine the wording\n   • A Personal/Team toggle to choose where to save\n\n3. User taps 'Save Prompt' to confirm.\n\n4. A success toast appears: 'Saved to My Prompts'.\n\n5. Saved prompts are accessible from the Prompts Library.\n\nRationale: This is the most natural moment of discovery — the user just got a response that worked well and wants to keep it. No hunting through settings."
    },
    {
      "type": "note",
      "id": "Y2bwL",
      "x": 55657,
      "y": 4821,
      "width": 250,
      "height": 219,
      "content": "Users can also access saved prompts, prompt library from the side bar so it is easily accessible\n"
    },
    {
      "type": "frame",
      "id": "2tXVs",
      "x": 280,
      "y": 1520,
